from IPython.display import HTML as html_print

In [24]:
data=pd.read_csv('district.csv')
In [25]:
Re=data.iloc[:30,5].values
De=data.iloc[:30,4].values
Co=data.iloc[:30,3].values
La=list(data.iloc[:30,0])
In [26]:
co=Co
re = Re
de=De
x = La

plt.figure(figsize=(25,10))

ax=plt.axes()
ax.set_facecolor('black')
ax.grid(linewidth=0.4, color='#8f8f8f')

plt.bar(x,co,label='re')
plt.bar(x,re,label='re',color='green')
plt.bar(x,de,label='re',color='red')

for i,j in zip(x,co):# numbers on graph
    ax.annotate(str(int(j)),xy=(i,j+3),color='white',size='15')

plt.xticks(rotation='vertical',size='20',color='white')#ticks of X
plt.yticks(size='20',color='white')

plt.legend(['Confirmed','Recovered','Deceased'],fontsize=20)


ax.set_xlabel('\nDistrict',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')#label of x
ax.set_ylabel('No. of cases\n',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')#label of y

plt.tick_params(size=20,color='white')# -

ax.set_title('Maharashtra District wise breakdown\n',size=50,color='#28a9ff')
print("Last Updated [30 April 2020]")

Last Updated [30 April 2020]

plt.figure(figsize=(25,8)) # creates canvas
ax = plt.axes() 

ax.grid(linewidth=0.4, color='#8f8f8f') #grid lines
ax.set_facecolor("black") #set background colour
ax.plot(X,Y,'o-',linewidth=4,markersize=10) #plot

for i,j in zip(X,Y):# annotation
    ax.annotate(str(j),xy=(i,j+25),color='white',size='15')
    
#X
ax.set_xlabel('\nDate',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')#label of X
plt.xticks(rotation='vertical',size='20',color='white')#ticks of X

#Y
ax.set_ylabel('Number of Confirmed Cases\n',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')# label of y
plt.yticks(size=20,color='white')# ticks of y

plt.tick_params(size=20,color='white')# '-'
plt.title("COVID-19 April : Daily Confrimed\n",size=50,color='#28a9ff')#title

## creating arrow
ax.annotate('Second Lockdown 15th April', xy=(15.2, 860),xytext=(19.9,630),color='white',size='25',
            arrowprops=dict(color='white',linewidth=0.025))

print("")

plt.figure(figsize=(30,11)) # creates canvas
ax = plt.axes() # get axes


ax.grid(linewidth=0.4, color='#8f8f8f') #grid lines
ax.set_facecolor("black") #set background colour

ax.plot(X,Y,'#1F77B4',marker='o',linewidth=4,markersize=15,markeredgecolor='#035E9B') #plot
ax.plot(X,D,'r',marker='X',linewidth=4,markersize=15,markeredgecolor='#c60027')
ax.plot(X,R,'g',marker='P',linewidth=4,markersize=15,markeredgecolor='#005400')

for i,j in zip(X,Y):# numbers on graph
    ax.annotate(str(j),xy=(i,j+30),color='white',size='15')
for i,j in zip(X,D):# numbers on graph
    ax.annotate(str(j),xy=(i,j-85),color='white',size='15')
for i,j in zip(X,R):# numbers on graph
    ax.annotate(str(j),xy=(i,j+40),color='white',size='15')

#X
ax.set_xlabel('\nDate',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')#label of x
plt.xticks(rotation='vertical',size='20',color='white')#ticks of X
#Y
ax.set_ylabel('Population\n',size=25,color='#4bb4f2')
plt.yticks(size=20,color='white')

plt.tick_params(size=20,color='white')# -
ax.set_title('COVID-19 IN April\n',size=50,color='#28a9ff')

ax.legend(['Confirmed','Deceased','Recovered'],loc="upper left",fontsize='17')

## creating arrow
ax.annotate('Second Lockdown 15th April', xy=(15.009,-87),xytext=(11.37, 2350),color='grey',size='25',
            arrowprops=dict(color='white',linewidth=0.5,arrowstyle='-'))
print("")
